Image thresholding¶

In [76]:
from skimage.filters import threshold_otsu,threshold_adaptive
from skimage.io import imread, imsave
from skimage.color import rgb2gray

img = imread('image.png')
img = rgb2gray(img)

thresh_value = threshold_otsu(img)
thresh_img = img > thresh_value

io.imshow(thresh_img)
io.show()

Edge detection¶

Sobel edge detector¶

sobel function takes a 2D array as input;therefore,you will have to convert the image into a grayscale image first.

In [77]:
from skimage import io
from skimage import filters
from skimage import color
img = io.imread("image.png")
img = color.rgb2gray(img)
edge = filters.sobel(img)
io.imshow(edge)
io.show()

Canny edge detector¶

Four major steps:

  1. Smoothing
  2. Finding the gradient
  3. Nonmaximal suppression
  4. Thresholding
In [81]:
from skimage import io
from skimage import feature
from skimage import color
img = io.imread("image.png")
img = color.rgb2gray(img)
edge = feature.canny(img,1)
io.imshow(edge)
io.show()

In [1]:
import skimage.transform as st
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
#matplotlib inline

# 
image = np.zeros((100, 100))  #
idx = np.arange(25, 75)    #25-74
image[idx[::-1], idx] = 255  # \
image[idx, idx] = 255        # /

# hough
h, theta, d = st.hough_line(image)

#.
fig, (ax0, ax1) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8, 6))
plt.tight_layout()

#
ax0.imshow(image, plt.cm.gray)
ax0.set_title('Input image')
ax0.set_axis_off()

#hough
ax1.imshow(np.log(1 + h))
ax1.set_title('Hough transform')
ax1.set_xlabel('Angles (degrees)')
ax1.set_ylabel('Distance (pixels)')
ax1.axis('image')
plt.show()


skimage.transform.hough_line_peaks(hspace, angles, dists

In [2]:
import skimage.transform as st
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 
image = np.zeros((100, 100))  #
idx = np.arange(25, 75)    #25-74
image[idx[::-1], idx] = 255  # \
image[idx, idx] = 255        # /

# hough
h, theta, d = st.hough_line(image)

#.
fig, (ax0, ax1,ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(8, 6))
plt.tight_layout()

#
ax0.imshow(image, plt.cm.gray)
ax0.set_title('Input image')
ax0.set_axis_off()

#hough
ax1.imshow(np.log(1 + h))
ax1.set_title('Hough transform')
ax1.set_xlabel('Angles (degrees)')
ax1.set_ylabel('Distance (pixels)')
ax1.axis('image')

#
ax2.imshow(image, plt.cm.gray)
row1, col1 = image.shape
for _, angle, dist in zip(*st.hough_line_peaks(h, theta, d)):
    y0 = (dist - 0 * np.cos(angle)) / np.sin(angle)
    y1 = (dist - col1 * np.cos(angle)) / np.sin(angle)
    ax2.plot((0, col1), (y0, y1), '-r')
ax2.axis((0, col1, row1, 0))
ax2.set_title('Detected lines')
ax2.set_axis_off()
plt.show()

canny

In [3]:
import skimage.transform as st
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from skimage import data,feature

#Probabilistic Hough Transform.
image = data.camera()
edges = feature.canny(image, sigma=2, low_threshold=1, high_threshold=25)
lines = st.probabilistic_hough_line(edges, threshold=10, line_length=5,line_gap=3)
print(len(lines))
# .
fig, (ax0, ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 6))
plt.tight_layout()

#
ax0.imshow(image, plt.cm.gray)
ax0.set_title('Input image')
ax0.set_axis_off()

#canny
ax1.imshow(edges, plt.cm.gray)
ax1.set_title('Canny edges')
ax1.set_axis_off()

#plot
ax2.imshow(edges * 0)
for line in lines:
    p0, p1 = line
    ax2.plot((p0[0], p1[0]), (p0[1], p1[1]))
row2, col2 = image.shape
ax2.axis((0, col2, row2, 0))
ax2.set_title('Probabilistic Hough')
ax2.set_axis_off()
plt.show()
